I think I've tried to use it however it does not  return what I would expect for `CPtrType` - in `CType` `can_coerce_to_pyobject` [is defined as](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/Cython/Compiler/PyrexTypes.py#L1635) 
```
    def create_from_py_utility_code(self, env):
        return self.from_py_function is not None

    def can_coerce_to_pyobject(self, env):
        return self.create_to_py_utility_code(env)
```
and for `CPtrType` `from_py_function` will not be `None`. As a result `can_coerce_to_pyobject` for `CPtrType` returns `True` which lead to compile time error downstream.
